Package: nedplayer
Section: utils
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends}
Description: player for NED scripting language demoscene productions
 NED Player is a runtime engine developed by bartoshe for executing
 productions written in the NED scripting language. It is primarily
 aimed at demoscene content, interactive presentations and simple
 games built with the Dead Deer framework.
 .
 The player reads a data/player.conf configuration file and must be
 launched from the directory containing it. It supports OpenGL
 rendering, OpenAL audio, Vorbis/Ogg music, JPEG 2000 images and
 TrueType fonts via FreeType.

Package: fonts-segoe
Section: fonts
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends}
Description: Segoe UI-compatible TrueType fonts by Steve Matteson
 This package provides TrueType fonts compatible with the Segoe UI
 family, designed by Steve Matteson. They are used by NED Player
 productions that rely on this typeface for their on-screen text
 rendering.

Package: nedscript-fire-tutorial
Section: demos
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 fonts-segoe,
 nedplayer,
 common-install-function-ddebs
Description: fire effect tutorial for NED Player
 This package contains the fire-effect tutorial shipped with the NED
 Player source tree. It demonstrates basic particle and palette
 animation techniques available through the NED scripting language
 and serves as a starting point for learning Dead Deer development.
